  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Health Response for drought affected population of 5 prioritized districts in Kandahar Province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In order to answer the needs of white areas population of the 5 following districts: Nesh, Shawalikot, Maywand, Zheray and Khakrez, YHDO proposes an emergency health response to four categories of drought-related health effects: 1) general health problems2) water-related disease 3) airborne and dust-related disease and 4) vector-borne disease. YHDO will also ensure the referral system to HF&#x2019;s managed by BPHS implementer. YHDO will enable the following mobile teams, for a total of 7 teams:
 1 mobile health team per district in Khakrez, Nesh, and Zheri
 2 mobile health teams in Maywand district
 2 mobile health teams in Shawalikot district

The total beneficiaries reached by the project will be 22500 individuals, as per target calculations details attached to the proposal. YHDO has been operating as the emergency actor in Kandahar since 2017 and has observed the impacts of the drought, especially in the last months. The severity of the drought is expected to increase and cause further famine and displacement in the districts affected. YHDO is currently implementing health, protection and nutrition project in collaboration with BARAN under OCHA funding.

YHDO has extended community network in hard to reach districts of Kandahar and operated where other actors are not present (white areas controlled by the insurgency). To be noted that YHDO is the only mobile actor operating in Nesh district at the moment. Therefore, access advantage should be considered as a plus point that will enable our organization to reach the most vulnerable individuals affected by the drought, which are located in remote villages. YHDO has performed drought assessment in July 2018 and distinguishes which areas of each district are mainly affected by the drought. YHDO intend to seve mainly host communities that are still in their places of origin. IDP&#x2019;s located in district centers of the districts targeted will also be considered. YHDO did not propose activities in second priority districts, as they are easily accessible for other actors. 

YHDO is able to deploy a team quickly, as soon as recruitment and procurement processes are completed. The organization has the office and permanent team in the province, running 4 different major projects, including 2 emergency projects in hard to reach districts. YHDO already has authorization from all relevant local authorities to operate in white areas of hard to reach districts targeted.</narrative>
  </description>
